fields.name: The Last Supper
fields.description: This iconic fresco portrays JesusÆ final meal with his disciples, capturing the moment of revelation of betrayal. Da VinciÆs use of perspective and composition creates a dramatic and influential religious scene.

fields.name: The Scream
fields.description: This expressionist masterpiece portrays a figure on a bridge screaming in agony against a tumultuous sky. Munch's use of bold colors and distorted forms evokes deep psychological anguish.

fields.name: The Birth of Venus
fields.description: This iconic work depicts Venus emerging from the sea on a shell, surrounded by mythological figures. BotticelliÆs use of classical themes and graceful lines highlights the RenaissanceÆs reverence for classical antiquity.

fields.name: Night Hawks
fields.description: This painting depicts a late-night diner scene with isolated figures, conveying themes of loneliness and urban alienation through HopperÆs characteristic use of light and shadow.

fields.name: The Persistence of Memory
fields.description: Known for its melting clocks draped over surreal landscapes, this iconic piece explores themes of time and reality, blending dream-like imagery with precise detail.

fields.name: Les Demoiselles d'Avignon
fields.description: A groundbreaking work in Cubism, this painting depicts five nude women with fragmented forms and aggressive lines, challenging traditional representations of the female form and space.

fields.name: Guernica
fields.description: A powerful anti-war mural, PicassoÆs "Guernica" captures the horrors of conflict through a monochromatic, fragmented composition. The paintingÆs scale and dramatic imagery convey a poignant message about the impact of war.

fields.name: Girl with a Pearl Earring
fields.description: Often called the "Mona Lisa of the North," this portrait captures a young girl with an enigmatic expression and an exquisite pearl earring. Vermeer's masterful use of light and color creates a captivating effect.

fields.name: Composition VIII
fields.description: An abstract work featuring bold shapes, vibrant colors, and dynamic forms. KandinskyÆs composition is a seminal example of abstract art, aiming to evoke emotion and visual harmony through non-representational elements.

fields.name: Starry Night
fields.description: A mesmerizing depiction of a swirling night sky over a quiet village, showcasing Van Gogh's emotional turbulence and distinctive brushwork. The painting is renowned for its vibrant colors and dramatic movement.

fields.name: Mona Lisa
fields.description: Arguably the most famous painting in the world, this Renaissance portrait is celebrated for its subjectÆs mysterious smile and da Vinci's intricate use of sfumato to achieve lifelike realism.

fields.name: American Gothic
fields.description: Featuring a farmer and his daughter with stern expressions, this painting is a quintessential example of American regionalism. Its detailed depiction of rural life and Gothic architecture evokes a sense of austerity.

fields.name: Water Lilies
fields.description: MonetÆs series captures the serene beauty of his garden pond with a focus on reflections and light. The impressionistic brushwork and use of color evoke a sense of tranquility and natural splendor.

fields.name: The Creation of Adam
fields.description: Part of the Sistine Chapel ceiling, this fresco illustrates the biblical moment God gives life to Adam. MichelangeloÆs dynamic composition and muscular figures have become iconic symbols of divine creation.
